<br>
Anyway, Skrim will probably grant you access sometime in the next day or so.  He usually does it in a large batch all at once.  Keeps his workload down I guess.<br>
<br>
If you want to try it by all means.  I was about to post another call for someone to try.  However, you'll probably end up having to do both Fear and Hate on alternating weeks.  2 reasons.  Memebers of KCoG will need stuff from both planes.  Dont expect rangers and druids and necro's to show up to Hate if you dont plan on running Fear raids.  But even more importantly than that, when you sign up days its sort of expected that you alternate planes as well.  That is, one week you do Hate, the next you do Fear.  This helps to rotate the number of guilds on through.  Otherwise, you'd have a bunch of guilds camped only in 1 plane for weeks at a time.<br>
<br>
As for days.  Well, thats rather iffy.  Right now the seeding is for next week, which is the week of the 4th.  I would say there's a good chance at getting a planar day somewhere...just not necessarily the one you want.<br>
<br>
Basicly you simply ask for a plane, say PoF or PoH and list the days that you want on the weekly selection thread.  Skrim posts this Monday morning and closes it on Tuesday night or Wednesday morning.  In the order that you want.  Generally if you really want one, you list all 7 days.  Unless you are first you cant gaurentee your first selection, although Skrim does try his best.  Saturdays are actually one of the easier days to get since most people dont want to be raiding all day on a Saturday it seems.  It also allows for maximum time on a plane, which is also helpful in case of a screwup.<br>
<br>
In general plan on a weeknight raid unless you are in the top 7 seed.  Especially if Saturday isnt a good option for you.<br>
<br>
As for being ready, well thats entirely up to you.  If you want I'll be willing to go up with you to help out, but the raid will still be yours.  I certainly wont stop you from making a major mistake.  I find its generally best to let people make their own mistakes and figure out solutions from there.  Not only does it help them, but it actually increases the respect people will have for you.  We all mess up, its how we clean it up that seperates the good from the ugly.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions feel free to drop me an email or post something here.<br>
<br>
